Titolo: Bugs Bunny: Crazy Castle 3

Anno: 1997

Descrizione: Bugs Bunny: Crazy Castle 3 (バックス・バニー クレイジーキャッスル3), is a platform game developed by Kemco as part of the Crazy Castle series. It was originally released as a Japan-exclusive Game Boy title in July 1997 called Soreyuke!! Kid: Go! Go! Kid (それゆけ！！ キッド Go! Go! Kid) starring the character Kid Klown. The title was later remade on the Game Boy Color to include colorized graphics and new characters from the Looney Tunes series, which was released in Japan in January 1999 by Kemco, and later that year in North America and Europe by Nintendo. It was followed by a sequel, Bugs Bunny in Crazy Castle 4, in 2000, which featured Lola Bunny.

Genere: Platform 

Valutazione: N/A
